    prompt: 'Execute final crisis recovery actions by implementing your family\'s long-term stability plan and transitioning from crisis mode to sustainable routines',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Transitioning from active crisis management to sustainable recovery requires deliberate action to implement the long-term plans you\'ve developed throughout the crisis period. Begin executing your post-crisis family structure, implement new routines that incorporate lessons learned, and gradually shift from emergency decision-making to normal family planning processes. This final implementation phase ensures your family emerges from the crisis stronger and better prepared for future challenges rather than simply returning to pre-crisis patterns that may have contributed to vulnerability.'
  },
  {
    id: 'prompt-51',
    prompt: 'Conduct a comprehensive family crisis debrief session to document lessons learned, update emergency plans, and strengthen resilience strategies',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'After managing a major family crisis, conducting a thorough debrief helps your family learn from the experience and improve future crisis preparedness rather than simply moving on without reflection. Schedule a structured family meeting to discuss what worked well, what could have been handled better, and what gaps in preparation became apparent during the crisis. Use these insights to update your emergency plans, strengthen weak areas in your family\'s crisis response capabilities, and create actionable improvements that will make your family more resilient and better prepared for any future challenges.'
  }
];</parameter>
</invoke>
